libfort
------------------------------------------
C/C++ library to create formatted ASCII tables for console applications

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.2-1
  libfort-devel-0.3.2-1bl1
  libfort0.3-0.3.2-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.14.5-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  ninja-1.9.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/seleznevae/libfort

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/seleznevae/libfort/archive/v0.3.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libfort-0.3.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libfort-0.3.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libfort-0.3.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfort-0.3.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfort0.3-0.3.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfort-devel-0.3.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libfort)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libfort.README
  /usr/share/doc/libfort/ChangeLog.md
  /usr/share/doc/libfort/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libfort/README.md

(libfort0.3)
  /usr/bin/cygfort-0.3.dll

(libfort-devel)
  /usr/include/fort.h
  /usr/include/fort.hpp
  /usr/lib/libfort.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libfort.pc

------------------

